<h1>Rationale for selection of data sources</h1>
<p>Investigate the various factors impacting the number of accidents in London</p>

<ul>
  <li>Used government websites to scrape populations of Greater London Boroughs</li>
  <li>Used national statistics websites to scrape population density for each Greater London Borough</li>
  <li>Used TfL API for information on accident statistics by Borough</li>
  <li>Weather CSV - historical data</li>
  <li>Shapley file for boundaries of each London ward</li>
</ul>
<div>

<h2>Data manipulation </h2>

<h3> Code Example of Data manipulation </h3>
<div class="highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">pandas</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">pd</span>

<span class="c1"># Assuming weather_data and fatal_accidents_df are already defined</span>

<span class="c1"># Extract the date component from the "time" column in weather_data</span>
<span class="n">weather_data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'date'</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">to_datetime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">weather_data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'time'</span><span class="p">])</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">dt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">date</span>

<span class="c1"># Extract the date component from the "date" column in fatal_accidents_df</span>
<span class="n">fatal_accidents_subset</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">fatal_accidents_df</span><span class="p">[[</span><span class="s1">'date'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'severity'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'borough'</span><span class="p">]]</span>
<span class="n">fatal_accidents_subset</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'date'</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">to_datetime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">fatal_accidents_subset</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'date'</span><span class="p">])</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">dt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">date</span>

<span class="c1"># Define a function to merge fatal_accidents_df with weather_data based on dates</span>
<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">merge_weather_data</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">group</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">merge</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">group</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">weather_data</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">on</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'date'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">how</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'inner'</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">drop</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">columns</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'time'</span><span class="p">])</span>

<span class="c1"># Group fatal_accidents_df by date, apply the merge_weather_data function, and concatenate the results</span>
<span class="n">combined_df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">fatal_accidents_subset</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">groupby</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'date'</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">apply</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">merge_weather_data</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># Reset index to remove multi-index created by groupby</span>
<span class="n">combined_df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">reset_index</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">drop</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">True</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">inplace</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">True</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># Print the combined DataFrame</span>
<span class="n">combined_df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">head</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">30</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

<h2>Insights</h2>

<h3>Converting latitude and longitude to geospatial points using GeoPandas</h3>
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">geopandas</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">gpd</span>
<span class="kn">from</span> <span class="nn">plotnine</span> <span class="kn">import</span> <span class="o">*</span>

<span class="c1"># Converting df_accidents to a GeoDataFrame</span>
<span class="n">gdf</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">gpd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">GeoDataFrame</span><span class="p">(</span>
    <span class="n">df_accidents</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">geometry</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">gpd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">points_from_xy</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df_accidents</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">lon</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">df_accidents</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">lat</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">crs</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"EPSG:4326"</span>
<span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># Extracting relevant columns</span>
<span class="n">gdf_plot</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">gdf</span><span class="p">[[</span><span class="s2">"id"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"geometry"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"borough"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"severity"</span><span class="p">]]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">copy</span><span class="p">()</span>

<span class="c1"># Plotting with plotnine</span>
<span class="n">base_plot</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">(</span>
    <span class="n">ggplot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">gdf_plot</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">geom_point</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">aes</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"geometry.x"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"geometry.y"</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">size</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">labs</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"Longitude"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"Latitude"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">title</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"Accident Locations by Severity"</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">theme_bw</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">base_plot</span>
</pre></div>
